---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../site.config';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy"
  description={`How ${SITE.name} handles visitor information: no cookies, no analytics, no tracking scripts, and email used only to respond to your inquiry.`}
>
  <header class="page-intro container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Privacy, briefly</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      This site is built to need almost nothing from you — so this policy is
      short and true.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose container">
    <h2>What this site collects</h2>
    <p>
      Nothing, actively. There are no cookies, no analytics, no advertising
      pixels, and no third-party scripts of any kind. The site's hosting
      provider (Cloudflare) keeps standard server logs — such as IP addresses
      and requested pages — for security and operations, as virtually all web
      hosts do.
    </p>

    <h2>If you email me</h2>
    <p>
      Anything you send by email is used only to respond to your inquiry and,
      if we work together, to run your project. Your information is never
      sold, shared for marketing, or added to a mailing list.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      Pages on this site link to external sites, such as GitHub and project
      sites I've built. Those sites have their own privacy practices.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If the site ever starts collecting anything beyond the above — for
      example, a contact form — this page will be updated first, plainly.
    </p>

    <h2>Questions</h2>
    <p>
      Ask any time via the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
